    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 17</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num017-P241v-L2_trl" n="2"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.004.016.trl.xml#Num016-P241v-L2_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And the Lord spoke to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             saying,</l>
                        <l n="2">‘Speak to Eleazar, son of Aaron,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             the priest, that he shall separate the censers out of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             blaze and sprinkle the fire |some distance| away, because they have
                            become holy.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="3">The censers of these sinners by their souls:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             and they shall make of them flat metal sheets for a covering of the
                            altar, because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             they brought them forward before the Lord, and they became holy, and
                            they shall be a sign
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             to the children of Israel.’</l>
                        <l n="4">And Eleazar, the priest, took
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the bronze censers that those who were burned had brought forward, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             they flattened them to do a covering for the altar:</l>
                        <l n="5">A memorial
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             to the children of Israel, so that no outsider, who is not
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             of the offspring of Aaron, shall come near to burn incense before the
                            Lord,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             and so he shall not be like Korah and as his congregation, as the Lord
                            said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             to him by the prophecy of Moses.</l>
                        <l n="6">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             all the congregation of the children of Israel murmured after daybreak
                            against Moses
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and against Aaron, saying, ‘You have killed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             the people of the Lord.’</l>
                        <l n="7">And it was, when the congregation was gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             against Moses and against Aaron that they turned
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             toward the tent of meeting, and, lo, the cloud covered it, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             divine Presence of the Lord appeared.</l>
                        <l n="8">And Moses and Aaron came
                            <milestone unit="page" n="242r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             before the tent of meeting.</l>
                        <l n="9">And the Lord spoke to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             saying,</l>
                        <l n="10">‘Get away from among this congregation,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             that I may consume them <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-017-seg001_trl" />in the blink of an eye<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Num-017-seg001_trl" /><ref n="1"
                                target="#Num-017-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" />.’ And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             they fell on their faces.</l>
                        <l n="11">And Moses said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             to Aaron, ‘Take a censer and put fire on it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             from off the altar and put on incense and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             carry it quickly to the congregation and ask for atonement for them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             because there is anger gone out from before the Lord. The plague has
                            begun.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="12">And Aaron took as Moses said, and ran
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             into the midst of the assembly, and, lo, the plague had begun
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             among the people. And he put on incense and asked for atonement
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             for the people.</l>
                        <l n="13">And he stood between
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             the dead and the living, and the plague ceased.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="14">And the dead in the plague were fourteen
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             thousand and seven hundred, apart from the dead over the matter of
                            Korah.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="15">And Aaron returned to Moses to the door of the tent of meeting,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             when the plague ceased.</l>
                        <l n="16">And the Lord spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="17">‘Speak to the children of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and take from them a staff, one for each of the house of their fathers,
                            from all their princes
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             by the house of their fathers, twelve staffs.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             You shall write each man’s name on his staff.</l>
                        <l n="18">And
                            <milestone unit="page" n="242v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             you shall write Aaron’s name on the staff of Levi, because there is one
                            staff
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             for the superior of the house of their fathers.</l>
                        <l n="19">And you shall place
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             them in the tent of meeting before the testimony, because my
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             divine Presence is ready to appear there to you.</l>
                        <l n="20">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             it shall be: the man <supplied reason="lost">I</supplied> shall choose
                            — his staff will blossom. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             I will suppress from me the murmurings of the children of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             which they murmur against you.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="21">And Moses spoke to the children of Israel, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             all of their princes gave him a staff, for each prince one,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             for each prince one, by their fathers’ house, twelve
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             staffs, and the staff of Aaron was among their staffs.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="22">And Moses placed the staffs before the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             in the tent of law.</l>
                        <l n="23">And it was after daybreak,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             and Moses came to the tent of law, and, lo,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             the staff of Aaron for the house of Levi blossomed and brought out a
                            leaf and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             and bloomed flowers, and yielded almonds.</l>
                        <l n="24">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             Moses brought out all the staffs from before the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             to all the children of Israel, and they looked, and took every man
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             his own staff.</l>
                        <l n="25">And the Lord said to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             ‘Bring Aaron’s staff back before the law,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             to be kept for the rebellious people, and you shall end their
                            murmurings
                            <milestone unit="page" n="243r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             against me, so they would not die.’</l>
                        <l n="26">And Moses did
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             so as the Lord commanded him, he did so.</l>
                        <l n="27">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             the children of Israel spoke to Moses, saying, ‘Lo,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             we died, we perished, we all perished.</l>
                        <l n="28">Everyone
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             who comes near to the tabernacle of the Lord dies.
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num017-P243r-L6_trl" n="6"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.018.trl.xml#Num018-P243r-L6_trl" />
                             Have we indeed come to the end of dying?’ </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
